      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHA CHA ETHICS (1) was well fancied in betting last start but could only manage 2.75 lengths away in second (29.97). Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Deserves a win and gets her chance. EXQUISITE ETHICS (3) is worth forgiving last start after finishing seventh (30.63) in a Grade 5 at Wentworth Park over 520m. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Likely to be thereabouts. FERRARI FIRE (2) doesn't win out of turn but looks close to breaking through. Continues to race well, filling the minors at the last three starts, the latest when second (22.77) at this track. Can measure up. ROAD TO FAME (8) has strong credentials at this circuit over this journey.",
